The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as object detection and segmentation using convolutional neural networks, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel architecture tailored for SDS, which involves the use of top-down figure-ground predictions, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses diagnostic tools for performance analysis, which could fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
